thread.title: Browse unveils Browse FLNG plans

title: Browse unveils Browse FLNG plans
text:
Wed, Jul 1, 2015, 9:58 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 mins. Browse unveils Browse FLNG plans AAP – 7 minutes ago Print 
Woodside Petroleum's Browse gas project is a step closer after it announced plans to begin designing the floating liquefied natural gas technology it will use. 
Woodside said agreement had been reached to enter the front-end engineering and design (FEED) phase for the proposed development, estimated to cost more than $80 billion. 
Woodside chief executive Peter Coleman said the decision to enter the FEED phase on Browse was a significant step towards developing the world class resources. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Greece's bailout expires, country defaults AAP
